Note: No changes required in NGIX Config file/etc/nginx/nginx.conf
/etc/nginx/sites-available/share.chartiq.com.conf
/etc/nginx/sites-available/services.chartiq.com.confThe SSL renewal is designed to work through the current symlink.Cert Deployment Steps 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step-1. Create a bew directory:Create a new SSL directory for the renewal.
sudo mkdir -p /etc/nginx/ssl/2026

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step-2. Copy New Certificate Files: 
Copy the following files received from the certificate team:chartiq.com.crt
DigiCertGlobalG2TLSRSASHA2562020CA1.crt
DigiCertGlobalRootG2.crt
chartiq.keyinto:     /etc/nginx/ssl/2026

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step-3 Validate Certificate and Private key Match 

Verify that the private key belongs to the certificate.

openssl rsa -noout -modulus -in /etc/nginx/ssl/2026/chartiq.key | openssl md5
openssl x509 -noout -modulus -in /etc/nginx/ssl/2026/chartiq.com.crt | openssl md5

Expected:Both MD5 values must be identical 
Example:
MD5(stdin)= abc123456
MD5(stdin)= abc123456If

values differ, STOP and contact the certificate provider


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step-4 Create chained certificate

Inside:

/etc/nginx/ssl/2026cat chartiq.com.crt DigiCertGlobalG2TLSRSASHA2562020CA1.crt > chartiq_com.chained.crt

Verify:grep -c "BEGIN CERTIFICATE" chartiq_com.chained.crt

Expected:2

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step-5  Set permissions
chown root:root *
chmod 600 chartiq.key
chmod 640 chartiq_com.chained.crt

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step-6 Verify current symlink

ls -l /etc/nginx/ssl/current

Should show something like:
current -> /etc/nginx/ssl/2025

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step-7  Switch symlink

sudo rm /etc/nginx/ssl/current

sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/ssl/2026 /etc/nginx/ssl/current

Verify:
ls -l /etc/nginx/ssl/current

Expected:current -> /etc/nginx/ssl/2026

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step-8 Validate NGINX

Critical step

sudo nginx -t

Expected:
nginx: configuration file /etc/nginx/nginx.conf test is successful

If this fails, stop and share the output

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

.Step-9  Reload / Restart NGINX

Since only certificates changed:

sudo systemctl reload nginx
(or) follow team procedure:
sudo systemctl restart nginx

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step-10 Verify new certificate

Check locally:

openssl s_client \
-connect localhost:443 \
-servername share.chartiq.com \
</dev/null 2>/dev/null | \
openssl x509 -noout -dates

Look at:notAfter=

Which Confirm it shows the new expiry date.

